<subSubSection id="D9F16554FF8CBA20B6E6FE84B1F3F3C8" pageId="48" pageNumber="667" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="915436DFFF8CBA20B6E6FE84B1F3F3C8" blockId="48.[755,1348,2378,2801]" lastBlockId="48.[141,1348,2808,3472]" pageId="48" pageNumber="667">
Prior to description, a single 1961 specimen of the species was regarded as 
<taxonomicName id="56EB4D5CFF8CBA20B11BFD6BB1C3F59A" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1839" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Austronomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="671" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">Austronomus australis</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="E9FC764FFF8CBA20B053FD53B6E6F59A" box="[1089,1216,2611,2644]" name="Australia" pageId="48" pageNumber="667">Australia</collectingCountry>
. In 1982 K. F. Koopman regarded this form as a race of A. 
<taxonomicName id="56EB4D5CFF8CBA20B79FFDEAB1DCF56D" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[909,1018,2698,2723]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Austronomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="667" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">australis</taxonomicName>
, but subsequent publications have treated it as a species. There has been some confusion over the parent genus. T. Iredale and E. Le G. Troughton proposed the novel genus 
<taxonomicName id="56EB4D5CFF8CBA20B061FD98B73AF4D7" box="[1139,1308,2808,2841]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Austronomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="667" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Austronomus</taxonomicName>
in 1934, but it wasinitially invalid; the name was validated by Troughton in 1941. 
<taxonomicName id="56EB4D5CFF8CBA20B0DAFC7FB2E5F4A6" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Austronomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="667" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Austronomus</taxonomicName>
was synonymized within the genus 
<taxonomicName id="56EB4D5CFF8CBA20B6A8FC27B10BF4A6" authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1814" box="[698,813,2887,2920]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Tadarida" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="667" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Tadarida</taxonomicName>
by J. E. Hill in 1961 and others; it was alternatively synonymized with Nyctinomus in 1988 by J. A. Mahoney and D. W. Walton and others. Subsequently, the genus 
<taxonomicName id="56EB4D5CFF8CBA20B688FCF6B165F479" box="[666,835,2966,2999]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Austronomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="667" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Austronomus</taxonomicName>
was again recognized for 
<taxonomicName id="56EB4D5CFF8CBA20B0ABFCF6B762F479" authorityName="McKean &amp; Calaby" authorityYear="1968" box="[1209,1348,2966,2999]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Tadarida" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="667" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kuboriensis">kuboriensis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="56EB4D5CFF8CBA20B4DDFCDDB31AF410" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[207,316,3005,3038]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Austronomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="667" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">australis</taxonomicName>
by L. K. Ammerman and colleagues in 2012 and T. B. Reardon and colleagues in 2014, and it currently remains in use. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
